race.comment: SUPER QUICK (6) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when 2.25 lengths away in second over 1400m at Gatton when he was in the firing line all the way. Likely improver with strong prospects. GALWAY HUSSLER (2) pushed forward when resuming last time and boxed on to finish 5 lengths away in third over 1100m at Toowoomba. Should park just off the speed despite a difficult draw. Has her share of ability and is hard to beat in this suitable race. AMENOPHIS (8) progressed nicely last time out to finish just 0.8 lengths from the winner in second over 1400m at Stanthorpe. Meeting a tougher field but on his best form he is one of the key runners. DEPTH CHARGE (1) next best with the 3kg claim.
